            <div type="l">
                <column>01</column>
                <head>To the Legislature of Virginia</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>The citizens of Augusta asked for an assessment of county lands so they can
                    benefit from an act passed for the protection of crops. They claimed to be
                    "great sufferers by the loss of fencing, crops, horses, mills, dams and serious
                    injury to lands, by the late freshet."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head/>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Stuart</ln>
                        <fn>A. H. H.</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>The paper urged the friends of "the great water line through this State
                    from East to West" to nominate and elect A. H. H. Stuart for Congress. Promised
                    that he would support improvements to the line.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
            </div>
            <pageNote/>
        </page>
